PROTESTORS RETURNED to the streets of Khartoum this weekend, again with deadly consequences. We look back to last month’s violent crackdown, and consider Sudan’s troubled push for democracy.China’s swine-flu outbreaks threaten hundreds of millions of pigs—but might spark long-overdue reforms in the country’s pork industry. And, we examine San Francisco’s e-cigarette ban: if vaping is safer than smoking, should it be stubbed out? Additional audio courtesy of Azzam al-Maryoud. Runtime: 22 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn